==English==

===Pronunciation===
*{{audio|en-us-strip.ogg|Audio (US)}}
*strĭp, /strɪp/, /<tt>strIp</tt>/
*:[[Rhymes:English:-ɪp|Rhymes: -ɪp]]

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# a long, thin piece of a bigger item
#* ''You use '''strips''' of paper in papier mache.''
# a series of drawings, a comic '''strip'''
# a [[landing strip]]
# a street with multiple shopping or entertainment possibilities
# {{fencing}} The fencing area, roughly 14 meters by 2 meters.
# ([[UK]] [[football]]) the [[uniform]] of a football team, or the same worn by [[supporter]]s.

